@startuml sync-vs-async
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Sequence.puml

title Synchronous vs Asynchronous

== Synchronous (request-response) ==

participant "Client" as C1
participant "API Gateway" as API1
participant "Lambda A" as A1
participant "Lambda B" as B1
participant "Lambda C" as C1b

C1 -> API1: POST /checkout
API1 -> A1: invoke
A1 -> B1: invoke (waits)
B1 -> C1b: invoke (waits)
C1b --> B1: response
B1 --> A1: response
A1 --> API1: response
API1 --> C1: response\n(slow if C is slow)

== Asynchronous (event-driven) ==

participant "Client" as C2
participant "API Gateway" as API2
participant "Lambda A" as A2
participant "EventBridge" as EB
participant "Lambda B\n(create subscription)" as B2
participant "Lambda C\n(generate invoice)" as C2b
participant "Lambda D\n(send email)" as D2

C2 -> API2: POST /checkout
API2 -> A2: invoke
A2 -> EB: publish "CheckoutCompleted"
A2 --> API2: 200 OK
API2 --> C2: response\n(immediate)
EB ->> B2: route event
EB ->> C2b: route event
EB ->> D2: route event

@enduml
